      "span_text": "For A. baumannii, passive immunization with DELTAtrxA-immune sera provided protection against lethal systemic challenge in mice. Anti-OMC antisera was shown to be highly protective, suggesting that vaccine antisera has the potential to treat established infections, including those caused by pan-resistant clinical isolates. The same group showed that passive immunization with serum raised against inactivated cells protects mice from subsequent infection."
